      <title>Re: What clerics need</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10746#M10746</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;What I'd like to see improvements in are the following:&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;1.&amp;nbsp; AC has been improved but is this something that is a done deal or is there still a chance that we'll get improved mitigation?&amp;nbsp; Personally, I'd like to see better mitigation.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;2.&amp;nbsp; Block or Parry skill.&amp;nbsp; Whatever would work best with a shield.&amp;nbsp; I don't know how the developers could resolve this because 'Block' is done by using the body and 'Parry' is done by using the weapon.&amp;nbsp; Anyway, it makes no sense whatsoever to have a shield and not be able to block with it.&amp;nbsp; What makes this even idea even more in line with the whole 'defensive' emphasis is the fact that our epic is a shield.&amp;nbsp; I'm not asking for a 'Defensive' mode like Warriors.&amp;nbsp; But, I want to be able to hide behind my shield when it gets real rough.&amp;nbsp; An epic shield should provide some good protection don't you think?&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;3.&amp;nbsp; Group Heal over Time.&amp;nbsp; We need an improved version.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;4.&amp;nbsp; Improved Panoply of Vie.&amp;nbsp; I'd even like to see a group version.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;5.&amp;nbsp; Improved resists buff.&amp;nbsp; Perhaps a Seasons-lite version.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;6.&amp;nbsp; Improved Avatar.&amp;nbsp; I know it's been updated but it is still sorely lacking.&amp;nbsp; Especially considering the recast time.&amp;nbsp; How about instead of a self-only HoT we have a group version with a group DS component also?&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;7.&amp;nbsp; In my opinion, the procs on all our summoned pets and hammers should have a group heal component to them.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;8.&amp;nbsp; DD spells are pathetic.&amp;nbsp; I will cast on occassion but the&amp;nbsp;Undead line is in dire need of upgrading.&amp;nbsp; We definitely aren't masters and we don't strike fear into the hearts of the undead.&amp;nbsp; The DoTs would be a great place to start.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;That should be good enough for now.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ffff00&gt;SS&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
