      <description>&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
brum wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Just tried to solo the Stillmoon portion of first part of DON progression---you know the kill 11 stillmoon laborers one.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;well buff up and put my new proccing damage shield on.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; summon hammer of reproach and head in to battle.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;mob hits me 93 times---proc goes off 6&amp;nbsp;times &amp;nbsp;after I had to cast it twice for fight duration.&amp;nbsp; **HALFLING**??&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I cast reproach 6 times---resisted 4 and only hit for 400 once.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; other hit for 1600 (murams)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;get mob to 10% life--it runs.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; resists both stuns and the root.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 4 mobs come back--I run and zone&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;lets try this again--huh&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2nd time around &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;mob hits me 61 times&amp;nbsp; get 7 procs---well better (but still mob is hitting me for 200+&amp;nbsp; times 60 is 12000 pts of damage so i can do 3150 back??&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; and it is interupting my casting the whole time?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;6 tries at reproach--3 resists.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 1 for 140 , 1 for 800, and 1 for 1400.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;mob gets down to 12%.&amp;nbsp; runs--resists two stuns and a root---3 mobs come back--I run and zone&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;wow lets make sure i succeed third time.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Log in wifes druid--join group--park cleric in corner.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;druid roots two laborers--dots both--sits down--gets up after a couple of minutes-reroots and redots both---snares both.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; both die.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; druid runs off and gets last laborer---roots and dots for a few minutes, snares it&amp;nbsp;then finishes it off with 3 back to back glitterfrost all scoreing above 3K.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;nice to see that the solo parts of the DON progression is so "bleeping" soloable for all classes.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;That part is eminently soloable for clerics ( I soloed 100 % of the solo stages of DoN in such wonderful gear as mail of judgement ) though the stillmoon goblins are by far the hardest of the lot. General way&amp;nbsp;to do it is &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Pull with annul - make sure you pull two. &amp;nbsp;Make sure you are always fighting two, even if you don't expect to kill the second. This removes runners from the equation. Zone line fighting makes fleeing trivial. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ignore nuking - it wastes mana - load up with kyva's skin of flame potion, double reverse damage shield and the self-proc-damage-shield. Load at least two stuns since there are an irritating number of cleric mobs in the zone. Have graphics on so you can see when they are casting long heals ( ie CH ) by the blue particle effect. &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ater this it is a battle of attition which 80 % of the time I could win, with my most recent gear being a year old.&amp;nbsp; As my mana preservation item is now my main hand weapon - and has no attack value -&amp;nbsp;I don't &amp;nbsp;even bother&amp;nbsp;meleeing in more recent soloing. Anyone who feels happy with a summoned hammer will do better DPS than I did. Besides, it confises passers by to see me soling just by standing around doing nothing, waggling a small stick in the air while creatures try to nibble my nose.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;On topic once more, I can solo 80 % of what druids can - I don't feel I need more.&amp;nbsp; I have accidentally killed several blue con nameds, the sort who are not capitalised and thus hard to spot.&amp;nbsp; If I went in all guns blazing and tried to nuke these to death I'd be dead meat.&amp;nbsp; Using the porcupine method makes them trivial.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
