    <item>
      <title>Re: What clerics need</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10570#M10570</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Fine, as I said, if you are dead set against shamans being a healer if they are also a slower, then you should be proposing another class as a viable top tier healer.&amp;nbsp; The other obvious candidate would be paladin, but of course they are&amp;nbsp;a top-3&amp;nbsp;tank, so they'd be equally overpowered if they were also a top-3 healer.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Unless you're going to&amp;nbsp; insist that your role only have 2 classes able to fill it, then it seems like your only option is to be pushing for a brand new healing class or picking a class that already has a role to fill it as the #3 choice.&amp;nbsp; Personally, I think having one class able to be "top 3" in two roles isn't as unbalancing as having only two classes able to fill a critical group slot, but that's just my probably biased personal opinion.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;BUT, if&amp;nbsp;SoE goes with what they seem to be planning, even after reinvisioning is done clerics will still be the clear #1 choice for main healer based on this "80%" target they've explicitly stated.&amp;nbsp; Being a clear 2nd or&amp;nbsp;3rd choice for a slot and a "top 3" or "top 9" (in the case of dps) choice for a second slot isn't quite as unbalancing as being "top 3" in two slots.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Anyhow, the only solution which you'd find acceptable given your obvious position regarding shamans would probably be that SoE introduce a brand new healing class with the next expansion or as you say, that they finish nerfing slow out of existence or strip it outright from shamans.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Since the shaman thing&amp;nbsp;clearly isn't going to happen, since 90% of the shamans in the game would quit if they did it, then you're left with pushing for a new healing class or simply accepting the idea that either the game will be short of healers, screwing over all the non-healers trying to form groups, or the existing healing classes will be overrepresented by design.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If you're cool with the existing healing classes being overrepresented by design, I don't see why you're so dead set against shamans being able to heal and thus potentially becoming somewhat overrepresented.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;In any case, I have no idea how this thread degenerated into the same old crap about class balance.&amp;nbsp; I'll try to rerail it.&amp;nbsp; Things that should happen which would help clerics:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;#1 - reduce the requirement (or perception) that you need a zillion clerics on raids so "real" clerics don't have to compete with people who only made clerics because their guild needed them, not because that's what they wanted to play&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;#2 - boost baseline melee dps for all classes to the point where it actually matters and they can add some measurable dps no matter what role they are filling (adding stackablity).&amp;nbsp; This would represent the largest benefit for classes with the lowest spell-based dps and thus be helpful for clerics but just "amusing" for classes whose spell-based dps would suffer significantly by screwing with melee.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;#3 - give clerics a couple more defensive "utility" spells or perhaps a 30-40% haste spell so they can fill the slower slot when no slower is available.&amp;nbsp; Essentially, make them a viable last resort to fill the slower slot&amp;nbsp;(adding stackablity).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Of course, as the game is currently balanced, none of these things are really needed.&amp;nbsp; But these are things that I'd think would be good to push for if non-cleric healing improvements start to erode the current cleric advantage.&amp;nbsp; #1 and #3 would help to address potential problems caused by non-cleric healing improvements.&amp;nbsp; #2 we should push for just because it's fun.&amp;nbsp; That it probably helps clerics more than any other non-melee class is just an added bonus.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
