    <item>
      <title>Re: What clerics need</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10580#M10580</link>
      <description>&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
brum wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;haste is not the only boost clerics would need.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; they would need a boost in dps up to at least shammy level also.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; and dps in a form they could contribute while healing.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; see that second defensive slot is expected to do other things also.&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Which part of "boost all classes melee dps to be reasonable" wasn't clear?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; That's your "boost in dps".&amp;nbsp; That second defensive slot is NOT expected to do&amp;nbsp;huge dps, otherwise enchanters would never be able to get that slot, which they clearly do get.&amp;nbsp; When I am in the slower role, most of the time the group doesn't notice nor care whether I do DPS or not.&amp;nbsp; I have never been asked if I have any nuke or dot damage foci/AA, and in fact I do not have most of them.&amp;nbsp; Yet groups are perfectly happy to have me be slower in any zone in the game because I know how to do my job well, get the mobs slowed asap without screwing up the agro excessively, and do my secondary role of throwing in patch heals and helping the primary healer out when needed.&amp;nbsp; DPS is a DISTANT third priority.&amp;nbsp; If you think it's a huge issue when you choose your defensive classes, then you are seriously in need of a rethink of the way you form groups.&amp;nbsp; It's when the defensive classes focus too much on offense that groups end up wiping when they shouldn't.&amp;nbsp; Offense is what defensive classes do when they've got nothing else to do, it's not in any way a requirement to acceptably fill the role.&amp;nbsp; We're not trying to make clerics the #1 choice for the slower role, just trying to make it possible for them to fill it.&amp;nbsp; And excess DPS is NOT a requirement for that; it's just something you want.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
witha&amp;nbsp; cleric and shammy you get healing + slow + haste + great dps from shammy pet with spirit of leopard, spirit of leopard on another group member and shammy two dots (top two shammy dots will do 850 pts of damage a tick themselves--which is almost 150 dps just for the two dots)--now add in pet and group member both proccing spirit of leopard constantly.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; see shammy adds much more then haste and slow in that spot&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Shamans do not have time to debuff, slow, patch heal, cast 2 dots on&amp;nbsp;every mob, cast two casts of panther on every pull, and manage their pet.&amp;nbsp; Groups do not expect this.&amp;nbsp; I never do it.&amp;nbsp; And not a single person has ever said boo about it.&amp;nbsp; If the content is so easy that I have time to do all that crap, then the mob wouldn't last enough to DoT it anyhow.&amp;nbsp; You have a very strange view of the world if you think this is the&amp;nbsp;expection groups have&amp;nbsp;of every slower.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
a cleric in second "defensive" slot would be adding only healing.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; many times his healing is going to be wasted (landing at same time as primary healers---dont have that problem with slow)&amp;nbsp;but he cant stop casting to do anything else unlike the slower that once mob is slowed can do other things.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; even adding haste--does not make up for around 200-250 dps a shaman adds after slowing.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Not trying to turn clerics into full fledged slowers.&amp;nbsp; Just trying to make them a more acceptable alternative when you happen to have multiple clerics wanting to be in the same group.&amp;nbsp; My haste suggestion is the single largest reason why clerics don't fill that role as well as they should.&amp;nbsp; Boosting melee to be significant closes the DPS gap you seem to be so worried about.&amp;nbsp; If the shaman is doing that 200 dps of spell damage he doesn't have time to be swinging his weapon, so the melee boost helps him not at all, but the cleric can certainly use the melee boost I suggested to contribute some reasonable amount of dps while keeping the mob "slowed" (via Vie + heals) and&amp;nbsp; the group hasted.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Frankly, I'm beginning to think that you aren't even thinking of the implications of my suggestions before saying they won't be enough.&amp;nbsp; You seem to be blinded by some personal vision of god-like shamans which doesn't match the reality that I've seen.&amp;nbsp; All of my suggestions would be upgrades to clerics, a class that seriously does not even need any upgrades at the moment compared to a bunch of seriously screwed over classes that can't get a group to save their lives.&amp;nbsp; Yet when I propose changes to help clerics get a seconary group role, you demand to turn them into shamans or boost them 5 other ways instead.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Seems like you want to have the best healing in the game by a mile, a near-monopoly on castable rezzes, wizard like DPS from your nukes, better tanking, better stunning, better pacify, the ability to cast snare, and about 100 other things I've seen you ask for on this and other threads before you'll be satisfied.&amp;nbsp; Well, good luck.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
