&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Right, that's why instead of meleeing, I'd probably cast panther or another dot as a shaman, not melee for 75dps.&amp;nbsp; What's a cleric going to do in between casts of Vie/Elixir/Light?&amp;nbsp; Melee.&amp;nbsp; So the cleric would use the 75 dps of melee and the shaman would continue to prefer the higher dps from casting more spells, assuming there's time to do so, as you suggest.&amp;nbsp; Thus the shaman will continue to have roughly the same dps, since he's using spells, whereas the cleric will get the extra dps from meleeing, which is what he does anyhow when he wants to add dps.&amp;nbsp; At least, that's what all the clerics I ever grouped with do when they want to toss in dps.&amp;nbsp; They prefer to save their somewhat limited mana pool for healing, rather than burning it on nukes.&amp;nbsp; I can't see how this isn't obvious, so I'm not sure I'm explaining it very well.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
your suggestion glowing , shows just how much you understand what a cleric does. I notice you cleric is 57,&amp;nbsp; is it a res bot by any chance ? Just high enough to get 96% res.&amp;nbsp; &#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ah yes, the standard argument:&amp;nbsp; "you're not as high level as me, so you're clueless".&amp;nbsp; Sorry, but there's a cleric in pretty much EVERY group I'm ever in.&amp;nbsp; And I watch what they do carefully, since I'm usually their backup. &amp;nbsp;And when they want to add DPS, they melee, thus a melee boost helps them more than most casters who use spells when they want to add dps.&amp;nbsp; When I want to add some extra DPS on my shaman, I cast extra spells.&amp;nbsp; 75dps worth of added melee would not change that.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Also you suggestion for cleric to effect slow by healing, slow is cast , get it to land then do other stuff. The cleric version is a full time role.&amp;nbsp; &#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;That's a crock.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;First of all, the shaman does more than that as a slower.&amp;nbsp; Malos + slow + HoT&amp;nbsp;+&amp;nbsp;2 Canni + a damage spell as time and spell gems permit.&amp;nbsp; Where exactly am i going to fit meleeing into that picture without losing spell dps or failing to do my primary job?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Let's look at the cleric in that role now.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The cleric in the primary healing slot will be dealing with&amp;nbsp;about 65-70% of the incoming damage, leaving the second cleric to deal with 35-40%.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Assuming that the first cleric is "full time", the second cleric clearly would not be, since he only has to heal half as much.&amp;nbsp; That&amp;nbsp;leaves him time to&amp;nbsp;do something else.&amp;nbsp; The something else I'm proposing is melee, since that's what every cleric I've&amp;nbsp; grouped with seems to think is the wisest form of DPS, allowing them to preserve their mana for emergencies.&amp;nbsp; I'd think a cleric in the same role as the shaman would be Tossing Vie + Elixir + either remedy or light as needed.&amp;nbsp; You really think that a cleric would have to chain cast lights in order to keep up with 35% of an XP mob's damage?&amp;nbsp; If so, I don't see how the primary healer has any hope in hell of keeping up with the 65% of the damage he'd be dealing with if he had a slower in that role.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Of course, this entire analysis entirely ignores the fact that dps from your defensive slots is largely irrelevent and simply isn't a prereq for getting them when groups form, otherwise beastlords would probably be the #1 choice for slower.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
This is the cleric board if you hadn't noticed, stuff affecting all classes is better on the veterans forum.&amp;nbsp; If you did what you suggest to all casters, it wouldn't make a blind bit of difference as the dps tree would be exactly the same. Clerics still bottom by a long way , for clerics to get to druid level dps you almost have to quadruple cleric dps. &#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I proposed the melee thing here because I think it's something reasonable which every class could get behind or simply not care about, but which would help clerics more than most caster classes.&amp;nbsp; If you instead prefer to propose cleric specific pipe dreams that would completely screw over game balance, go for it.&amp;nbsp; Or you could propose a cleric specific flavor of it and ask for them to move you to the same melee table as bards, just as they did with your armor.&amp;nbsp; Other classes, instead of supporting you though, will ask why clerics, already the most groupable class in the game, need even more groupability.&amp;nbsp; The difference here is that I'm proposing stuff that will help,&amp;nbsp; and that has a hope of happening.&amp;nbsp; While others are proposing stuff which either isn't gonna happen in a million years, or will happen despite jealous protests from other classes.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;And this business about adding a fixed amount to each class not making any difference is clearly wrong.&amp;nbsp; Let's use something you understand well to demonstrate.&amp;nbsp; If they added say 5000 hp healed to all priest 3.75 cast time "light" heals, would that leave the effective pecking order the same among healers or would it seriously cut into the current cleric advantage?&amp;nbsp; Right, it would largely eliminate any significant difference between the healers.&amp;nbsp; Adding a fixed amount to everyone helps the people at the bottom the most.&amp;nbsp; Period.&amp;nbsp; The math to prove it is obvious:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;class A (let's call them "druid") does 300 dps.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;class B (let's call them "cleric") does 100 dps.&amp;nbsp; -- class A is 3 times better than class B.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What happens if we add 100 dps to each?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Class A does 400 dps.&amp;nbsp; -- class A is only 2 times better than class B now.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Class B does 200 dps.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As you can clearly see, adding a fixed amount is a boost to the class at the bottom.&amp;nbsp; Now add in the fact that the way I added it favors the lower dps class, since it matches the way they already do DPS, whereas it would reduce the dps of the higher dps class since it would take either casting time or med time away.&amp;nbsp; And what do you get?&amp;nbsp; Right!&amp;nbsp; You get even more of a relative boost for the lower class.&amp;nbsp; This seems obvious to me.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
When the hammer came live, they were better dps, that lasted less than 24 hours before they were reduced due to complaints , your suggestion would have exactly the same effect.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Why?&amp;nbsp; This is not at all obvious and just seems like the standard "but they nerfed our hammer so we're screwed" thing I've seen a zillion times before.&amp;nbsp; I suppose you still think the 10 second heal they gave shamans at that same time is a huge nerf to clerics despite the fact that shamans never use it?&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by GlowingRune on &lt;span class=date_text&gt;11-30-2005&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=time_text&gt;04:01 PM&lt;/span&gt;</description>
