      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Glowing you make good arguments.&amp;nbsp; However, the primary healer can toss Vie pre-fight (I know I do) and Elixir can also be done by the primary healer (that's a style and situation thing).&amp;nbsp; And both of these things happen in a healer + slower configuration.&amp;nbsp; So, all that you've accomplished is split the mana cost between two healers.&amp;nbsp; The second healer still has to throw at least a couple of fast heals (if not three or four) to make up for the lack of slow.&amp;nbsp; Yes, if the two cleics comminucate properly healing overlap should be at a minimum.&amp;nbsp; However, the mana usage of the second cleric is FAR more than what a slower has to use to tash/malo + slow, unless a chain cheal&amp;nbsp;rotation is used in which case both neither could DPS.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
